===Interjection===
Term meaning "What a mess!" or "What a screw-up!"

'''Example:'''
*''Beautiful!  I dropped the soup on the floor!''

'''''Usage Note:''''' ''Beautiful'' can also be exclaimed by someone to mean "What a thing of beauty!"  ('''Example:'''  ''Beautiful!  What a catch! Phi-Ha is beautiful on the outside and inside'' [referring to an athlete catching a ball]).  In this usage, ''beautiful'' would generally be labeled an adjective, not an interjection.


